Class JacksonInnerQuantity

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.wikidata.wdtk.datamodel.json.jackson.datavalues.JacksonInnerQuantity

  • public class JacksonInnerQuantity
extends Object
    Helper object that represents the JSON object structure that is used to represent values of type JacksonValue.JSON_VALUE_TYPE_QUANTITY.
    Author:
    Fredo Erxleben

      • getJsonUnit

        public String getJsonUnit()
        Returns the string to use for the "unit" field in JSON. The value "1" is used to denote "no unit"; otherwise an IRI is used to denote specific units.
        Returns:
        unit string

      • setJsonUnit

        public void setJsonUnit(String unit)
        Sets the lower bound to the given value. Only for use by Jackson during deserialization.
        Parameters:
        unit - new unit value, the string "1" is used in JSON to denote that there is no unit for a quantity
